Report: Capabilities

The Capabilities Project (aka. Project Fugu 游냐) is a cross-company effort at Google to make it possible for web apps to do anything native apps can, by exposing the capabilities of native platforms to the web platform, while maintaining user security, privacy, trust, and other core tenets of the web.

  • (游냐 Launched) Async Clipboard Read
  • (游냐 Launched) Async Clipboard Write
  • (游냐 Launched) Badge Set
  • (游냐 Launched) Badge Clear
  • (游냐 Launched) Contact Picker
  • (游냐 Launched) Get Installed Related Apps
  • (游냐 Launched) Periodic Background Sync Register
  • (游냐 Launched) Periodic Background Sync
  • (游냐 Launched) Shape Detection (Barcode)
  • (游냐 Launched) Storage Estimation
  • (游냐 Launched) Persistent Storage
  • (游냐 Launched) Web OTP
  • (游냐 Launched) Web USB
  • (游냐 Launched) Web Bluetooth
  • (游냐 Launched) Web MIDI
  • (游냐 Launched) Screen Wake Lock
  • (游냐 Launched) Text Fragment
  • (游냐 Launched) Web Share (Containing Files)
  • (游냐 Launched) Web Share (No Files)
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Notification Triggers
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Web NFC (Read)
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Web NFC (Write)
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Web Serial
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Native File System
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Content Indexing
  • (游빍 Origin trial) QuicTransport
  • (游빍 Origin trial) Idle Detection
  • (游빍 Origin trial) WebSocketStream
  • (游뛀 Behind flag) Shape Detection (Face)
  • (游뛀 Behind flag) Shape Detection (Text)
